00:03:36.149 --> 00:03:38.854
Let's go to 4/9 d u.

00:03:38.854 --> 00:03:41.487
And then we just have to change
the bounds of integration.

00:03:41.487 --> 00:03:46.487
When x is equal to zero, then
u is going to be equal to...

00:03:48.781 --> 00:03:51.262
9/4 times zero is just zero, so u is going

00:03:51.262 --> 00:03:52.936
to be equal to one.

00:03:52.936 --> 00:03:57.936
And when x is equal to 32/9--

00:03:59.975 --> 00:04:01.458
and this is why that number was picked--

00:04:01.458 --> 00:04:03.602
what's u going to be equal to?

00:04:03.602 --> 00:04:07.936
32/9 times 9/4 is gonna be 32/4,

00:04:07.936 --> 00:04:09.992
which is going to be eight plus one.

00:04:09.992 --> 00:04:13.011
So that worked out very
nicely; imagine that.

00:04:13.011 --> 00:04:13.797
So there we have it.

00:04:13.797 --> 00:04:17.636
So, this is going to be equal
to the definite integral...

00:04:17.636 --> 00:04:18.998
Actually, let me make
it clear that this is

00:04:18.998 --> 00:04:20.349
what is equal to this.

00:04:20.349 --> 00:04:25.349
The definite integral
from u is equal to one,

00:04:25.517 --> 00:04:27.589
to u is equal to 9--

00:04:27.589 --> 00:04:28.922
I'm gonna make it very
explicit that I'm dealing

00:04:28.922 --> 00:04:30.839
with u now--

00:04:30.839 --> 00:04:35.488
of the square root of u.

00:04:35.488 --> 00:04:40.152
And instead of d x, we
have d x is 4/9 d u.

00:04:40.152 --> 00:04:43.760
Let me do it this way: the square root...

00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:45.909
Whoops, that's not the right color.

00:04:45.909 --> 00:04:50.909
Square root of u; instead of
d x, we have times 4/9 d u.

00:04:52.880 --> 00:04:57.880
And I'm just gonna take the
4/9 and stick it out here.

00:04:58.178 --> 00:05:01.597
And we know how to apply the fundamental,

00:05:01.597 --> 00:05:04.329
or, I guess, the second fundamental
theorem of calculus here,

00:05:04.329 --> 00:05:06.663
to evaluate this definite integral.

00:05:06.663 --> 00:05:11.663
This is going to be 4/9
times the anti-derivative

00:05:12.446 --> 00:05:15.030
of the square root of u,
which is the same thing

00:05:15.030 --> 00:05:16.551
as u to the 1/2.

00:05:16.551 --> 00:05:19.564
It's going to be u to the
3/2, and then we divide

00:05:19.564 --> 00:05:23.204
by 3/2, which is the same
thing as multiplying by 2/3.

00:05:23.204 --> 00:05:26.371
We're going to evaluate
that at u equals nine

00:05:26.371 --> 00:05:28.886
and u is equal to one.

00:05:28.886 --> 00:05:31.427
And so, we're in the home stretch here.

00:05:31.427 --> 00:05:36.427
This is going to be equal
to 4/9 times 2/3 times 9

00:05:41.641 --> 00:05:46.641
to the 3/2 minus 2/3 times one to the 3/2.

00:05:49.636 --> 00:05:52.119
So, 9 to the 3/2, that is...

00:05:52.119 --> 00:05:54.724
Let's see: the square
root of nine is three,

00:05:54.724 --> 00:05:57.302
